{\an8} [Adûnaic] ♫ <i>...îdô Nidir...</i> ♫
{\an8} [English] ♫ ...now the Nine... ♫

747
01:03:47,487 --> 01:03:50,987
{\an8} [Adûnaic] ♫ <i>...nênâ-kham, nêpâm...</i> ♫
{\an8} [English] ♫ ...we come, we grasp... ♫

748
01:03:53,011 --> 01:03:57,011
{\an8} [Adûnaic] ♫ <i>...abarat aglar.</i> ♫
{\an8} [English] ♫ ...power and glory. ♫

749
01:04:55,056 --> 01:04:56,456
What are they?

750
01:04:58,656 --> 01:05:00,756
They were once men.

751
01:05:01,056 --> 01:05:03,156
Great kings of men.

752
01:05:03,530 --> 01:05:06,756
Then Sauron the Deceiver gave to them
nine rings of power.

753
01:05:07,556 --> 01:05:10,556
Blinded by their greed,
they took them without question.

754
01:05:10,856 --> 01:05:13,755
One by one, falling into darkness.

755
01:05:14,356 --> 01:05:16,756
Now they are slaves to his will.

756
01:05:19,257 --> 01:05:20,857
They are the Nazgûl.

757
01:05:20,857 --> 01:05:23,657
Ringwraiths. Neither living nor dead.

758
01:05:24,657 --> 01:05:26,057
At all times they feel...

759
01:05:26,057 --> 01:05:28,057
... the presence of the ring...

760
01:05:28,357 --> 01:05:32,657
...drawn to the power of the One.
They will never stop hunting you.

761
01:05:42,857 --> 01:05:45,658
- Where are you taking us?
- Into the wild.

762
01:05:54,058 --> 01:05:57,858
How can we know this Strider
is a friend of Gandalf?

763
01:05:58,258 --> 01:06:01,058
I think a servant of the
enemy would look fairer...

764
01:06:01,458 --> 01:06:05,258
...and feel fouler.
- He's foul enough.

765
01:06:05,958 --> 01:06:08,283
We have no choice but to trust him.

766
01:06:09,074 --> 01:06:12,398
- But where is he leading us?
- To Rivendell, Master Gamgee.

767
01:06:14,759 --> 01:06:17,959
- To the house of Elrond.
- Did you hear that? Rivendell.

768
01:06:18,659 --> 01:06:21,359
We're going to see the elves.

769
01:06:43,060 --> 01:06:47,160
- Gentlemen, we do not stop till nightfall.
- What about breakfast?

770
01:06:47,460 --> 01:06:50,160
- You've already had it.
- We've had one, yes.

771
01:06:50,185 --> 01:06:52,162
What about second breakfast?

772
01:06:55,986 --> 01:06:58,631
I don't think he knows
about second breakfast, Pip.

773
01:06:59,460 --> 01:07:04,461
What about elevenses? Luncheon?
Afternoon tea? Dinner? Supper?

774
01:07:04,861 --> 01:07:08,861
- He knows about them, doesn't he?
- I wouldn't count on it.

775
01:07:14,461 --> 01:07:16,061
Pippin!

776
01:07:32,562 --> 01:07:35,862
