[English] Waters of the Misty Mountains, listen to the great word!

881
01:22:56,748 --> 01:23:00,128
[Sindarin] <i>Rimmo nîn Bruinen dan in Ulaer!</i>
[English] Flow waters of Loudwater against the Ringwraiths!

882
01:23:27,459 --> 01:23:36,259
{\an8} [English] ♫ What Grace... ♫

883
01:23:29,899 --> 01:23:32,299
No. No!

884
01:23:35,599 --> 01:23:37,799
Frodo, no.

885
01:23:36,260 --> 01:23:47,261
{\an8} [English] ♫ ...is given me... ♫

886
01:23:38,099 --> 01:23:40,299
Frodo, don't give in.

887
01:23:40,599 --> 01:23:42,499
Not now.

888
01:23:47,262 --> 01:23:57,062
{\an8} [English] ♫ ...let it pass... ♫

889
01:23:53,600 --> 01:23:56,000
What grace is given me...

890
01:23:56,700 --> 01:23:58,500
...let it pass to him.

891
01:23:57,063 --> 01:23:59,063
{\an8} [English] ♫ ...to him. ♫

892
01:23:58,800 --> 01:24:00,900
Let him be spared.

893
01:23:59,760 --> 01:24:12,561
{\an8} [English] ♫ Let him be spared. Mighty Valar, save him.  ♫

894
01:24:01,600 --> 01:24:03,500
Save him.

895
01:24:05,460 --> 01:24:09,551
[Sindarin] <i>Lasto beth nîn. Tolo dan nan galad.</i>
[English] Hear my voice. Come back to the light.

896
01:24:16,001 --> 01:24:21,001
- Where am I?
- You are in the house of Elrond.

897
01:24:21,601 --> 01:24:27,801
And it is 10 o'clock in the morning
on October 24th, if you want to know.

898
01:24:30,101 --> 01:24:33,701
- Gandalf!
- Yes, I'm here.

899
01:24:35,602 --> 01:24:38,502
And you're lucky to be here too.

900
01:24:39,202 --> 01:24:43,102
A few more hours and you would
have been beyond our aid.

901
01:24:43,502 --> 01:24:47,402
But you have some strength in you,
my dear Hobbit.

902
01:24:55,202 --> 01:24:57,602
What happened, Gandalf?

903
01:24:58,602 --> 01:25:03,000
- Why didn't you meet us?
- I am sorry, Frodo.

904
01:25:08,703 --> 01:25:10,403
I was delayed.

905
01:25:11,503 --> 01:25:15,503
A friendship with Saruman
is not lightly thrown aside.

906
01:25:19,803 --> 01:25:24,303
One ill turn deserves another. It is over.

907
01:25:24,803 --> 01:25:27,404
Embrace the power of the ring...

908
01:25:28,104 --> 01:25:30,504
...or embrace your own destruction!

909
01:25:32,904 --> 01:25:36,604
There is only one lord of the ring.

910
01:25:37,104 --> 01:25:40,904
Only one who can bend it to his will.

911
01:25:41,904 --> 01:25:45,704
And he does not share power.

912
01:26:00,105 --> 01:26:03,305
So you have chosen...death.

913
01:26:13,605 --> 01:26:17,205
Gandalf? What is it?

914
01:26:18,406 --> 01:26:20,106
Nothing, Frodo.

915
01:26:20,806 --> 01:26:22,706
Frodo!

916
01:26:24,106 --> 01:26:26,306
- Sam.
- Bless you, you're awake!

917
01:26:26,706 --> 01:26:29,306
Sam has hardly left your side.

918
01:26:29,588 --> 01:26:31,816
We were that worried about you.
Weren't we, Mr. Gandalf?

919
01:26:32,306 --> 01:26:37,206
By the skills of Lord Elrond,
you're beginning to mend.

920
01:26:38,697 --> 01:26:42,306
Welcome to Rivendell, Frodo Baggins.

921
01:27:30,508 --> 01:27:33,608
- Bilbo!
- Hello, Frodo, my lad.

922
01:27:34,008 --> 01:27:35,709
Bilbo.

923
01:27:40,609 --> 01:27:42,609
There and back again

924
01:27:42,609 --> 01:27:45,309
A hobbit's Tale, by Bilbo Baggins.''

925
01:27:48,509 --> 01:27:51,909
- This is wonderful.
- I meant to go back...

926
01:27:52,309 --> 01:27:56,009
...wonder at the powers of Mirkwood...

927
01:27:56,609 --> 01:27:58,809
...visit Lake-town...

928
01:27:59,109 --> 01:28:02,410
...see the Lonely Mountain again.

929
01:28:03,110 --> 01:28:07,710
But age, it seems, has
finally caught up with me.

930
01:28:20,110 --> 01:28:21,810
I miss the Shire.

931
01:28:22,310 --> 01:28:27,211
I spent all my childhood pretending
I was off somewhere else.

932
01:28:27,711 --> 01:28:30,496
Off with you, on one of your adventures.

933
01:28:34,111 --> 01:28:37,611
But my own adventure turned out
to be quite different.

934
