My dear boy.

936
01:28:53,912 --> 01:28:57,612
- Now, what have I forgotten?
- Packed already?

937
01:28:58,512 --> 01:29:00,212
No harm in being prepared.

938
01:29:00,517 --> 01:29:03,017
- I thought you wanted to see the elves.
- I do.

939
01:29:03,172 --> 01:29:05,391
- More than anything.
- I did.

940
01:29:06,412 --> 01:29:08,312
It's just....

941
01:29:08,926 --> 01:29:11,154
We did what Gandalf wanted, didn't we?

942
01:29:11,682 --> 01:29:14,465
We got the ring this far, to Rivendell.
And I thought...

943
01:29:15,384 --> 01:29:18,560
...seeing as how you're on the mend,
we'd be off soon.

944
01:29:19,313 --> 01:29:20,913
Off home.

945
01:29:25,057 --> 01:29:27,013
You are right, Sam.

946
01:29:29,313 --> 01:29:32,013
We did what we set out to do.

947
01:29:32,613 --> 01:29:35,113
The ring will be safe in Rivendell.

948
01:29:39,142 --> 01:29:41,202
I am ready to go home.

949
01:29:42,413 --> 01:29:44,314
His strength returns.

950
01:29:44,614 --> 01:29:50,114
That wound will never fully heal.
He will carry it the rest of his life.

951
01:29:51,014 --> 01:29:53,414
And yet to have come so far still bearing the ring...

952
01:29:53,414 --> 01:29:57,214
...the Hobbit has shown extraordinary
resilience to its evil.

953
01:29:57,430 --> 01:30:00,436
It is a burden he should never have had to bear.

954
01:30:01,035 --> 01:30:06,414
- We can ask no more of Frodo.
- Gandalf, the enemy is moving.

955
01:30:06,632 --> 01:30:11,081
Sauron's forces are massing in the East.
His eye is fixed on Rivendell.

956
01:30:11,715 --> 01:30:14,315
And Saruman, you tell me, has betrayed us.

957
01:30:14,567 --> 01:30:16,810
Our list of allies grows thin.

958
01:30:18,615 --> 01:30:21,026
His treachery runs deeper than you know.

959
01:30:21,516 --> 01:30:25,115
By foul craft, Saruman
has crossed orcs with goblin-men.

960
01:30:25,515 --> 01:30:27,815
He's breeding an army
in the caverns of Isengard.

961
01:30:28,215 --> 01:30:32,347
An army that can move in sunlight
and cover great distance at speed.

962
01:30:32,705 --> 01:30:35,310
Saruman is coming for the ring.

963
01:30:35,816 --> 01:30:39,182
This evil cannot be concealed
by the power of the elves.

964
01:30:39,994 --> 01:30:43,464
We do not have the strength to
fight both Mordor and Isengard!

965
01:30:48,155 --> 01:30:49,155
Gandalf...

966
01:30:50,555 --> 01:30:52,441
...the ring cannot stay here.

967
01:31:12,656 --> 01:31:15,284
This peril belongs to all Middle-earth.

968
01:31:16,056 --> 01:31:18,756
They must decide now how to end it.

969
01:31:19,856 --> 01:31:23,256
The time of the elves is over.
My people are leaving these shores.

970
01:31:24,056 --> 01:31:27,557
Who will you look to when we've gone?
The dwarves?

971
01:31:27,957 --> 01:31:32,857
They hide in mountains seeking riches.
They care not for the troubles of others.

972
01:31:34,557 --> 01:31:37,357
It is in men that we must place our hope.

973
01:31:37,758 --> 01:31:38,921
Men?

974
01:31:40,356 --> 01:31:43,201
Men are weak. The race of men is failing.

975
01:31:43,857 --> 01:31:48,057
The blood of Numenor is all but spent,
its pride and dignity forgotten.

976
01:31:48,557 --> 01:31:51,452
It is because of men the ring survives.

977
01:31:52,358 --> 01:31:53,858
I was there, Gandalf.

978
01:31:54,658 --> 01:31:57,358
I was there 3000 years ago...

979
01:32:04,158 --> 01:32:06,458
... when Isildur took the ring.

980
01:32:06,858 --> 01:32:10,558
I was there the day the
strength of men failed.

981
01:32:13,258 --> 01:32:15,758
Isildur, hurry! Follow me.

982
01:32:17,458 --> 01:32:20,959
I led Isildur into the
heart of Mount Doom...

983
01:32:21,359 --> 01:32:24,759
...where the ring was forged,
the one place it could be destroyed.

984
01:32:24,759 --> 01:32:26,865
Cast it into the fire!

985
01:32:32,759 --> 01:32:36,359
- Destroy it!
- No.

986
01:32:37,859 --> 01:32:39,959
Isildur!

987
01:32:40,459 --> 01:32:45,060
It should have ended that day,
but evil was allowed to endure.

988
01:32:49,360 --> 01:32:53,460
Isildur kept the ring.
The line of kings is broken.

989
01:32:54,460 --> 01:32:58,060
There's no strength
left in the world of men.

990
01:32:58,460 --> 01:33:03,060
- They're scattered, divided, leaderless.
- There is one who could unite them.

991
01:33:03,460 --> 01:33:06,660
One who could reclaim the throne of Gondor.

992
01:33:08,560 --> 01:33:11,294
He turned from that path a long time ago.

993
01:33:12,461 --> 01:33:14,561
He has chosen exile.

994
01:33:45,662 --> 01:33:47,562
You are no elf.

995
01:33:47,862 --> 01:33:49,862
Men of the South are welcome here.

996
01:33:50,562 --> 01:33:53,962
- Who are you?
- I am a friend to Gandalf the Grey.

997
01:33:55,562 --> 01:33:58,262
Then we are here on common purpose...

998
01:33:58,662 --> 01:34:00,062
...friend.

999
01:34:15,463 --> 01:34:18,263
The shards of Narsil.

1000
01:34:21,863 --> 01:34:26,063
The blade that cut the
ring from Sauron's hand.

1001
01:34:29,164 --> 01:34:31,364
It's still sharp.

1002
01:34:40,364 --> 01:34:43,264
But no more than a broken heirloom.

1003
01:35:10,265 --> 01:35:12,343
Why do you fear the past?

1004
01:35:14,165 --> 01:35:19,266
You are Isildur's heir,
not Isildur himseIf.

1005
01:35:19,766 --> 01:35:23,066
You are not bound to his fate.

1006
01:35:23,666 --> 01:35:27,466
The same blood flows in my veins.

1007
01:35:30,666 --> 01:35:33,166
The same weakness.

1008
01:35:35,966 --> 01:35:38,666
Your time will come.

1009
01:35:38,966 --> 01:35:43,166
You will face the same evil.
And you will defeat it.

1010
01:35:46,027 --> 01:35:48,737
[Sindarin] <i>A si i-Dhúath ú-orthor, Aragorn.</i>
[English] The shadow does not hold sway yet, Aragorn.

1011
01:35:49,727 --> 01:35:53,317
[Sindarin] <i>Ú or le a ú or nin.</i>
[English] Not over you, not over me.

1012
01:36:04,477 --> 01:36:07,717
[Sindarin] <i>Renich i lú i erui govannem?</i>
[English] Do you remember when we first met?

1013
01:36:11,208 --> 01:36:15,238
[Sindarin] <i>Nauthannen i ned ôl reniannen.</i>
[English] I thought I had strayed into a dream.

1014
01:36:16,138 --> 01:36:18,818
[Sindarin] <i>Gwenwin in enninath.</i>
[English] Long years have passed.

1015
01:36:19,858 --> 01:36:23,518
[Sindarin] <i>Ú-'arnech in naeth i si celich.</i>
[English] You did not wear the troubles you carry now.

1016
01:36:25,358 --> 01:36:27,658
[Sindarin] <i>Renich i beth i pennen?</i>
[English] Do you remember what I told you?

1017
01:36:33,868 --> 01:36:36,469
You said you'd bind yourself to me...

1018
01:36:38,669 --> 01:36:43,369
...forsaking the immortal
life of your people.

1019
01:36:44,669 --> 01:36:46,569
And to that I hold.

1020
01:36:46,569 --> 01:36:50,269
I would rather share
one lifetime with you...

1021
01:36:50,641 --> 01:36:54,241
...than face all the
ages of this world alone.

1022
01:37:03,270 --> 01:37:06,570
I choose a mortal life.

1023
01:37:08,070 --> 01:37:12,170
- You cannot give me this.
- It is mine to give to whom I will...

1024
01:37:15,570 --> 01:37:17,970
...like my heart.

1025
01:37:33,871 --> 01:37:37,471
Strangers from distant
lands, friends of old...

1026
01:37:37,871 --> 01:37:41,571
...you've been summoned here
to answer the threat of Mordor.

1027
01:37:42,371 --> 01:37:47,071
Middle-earth stands upon the brink of destruction.
None can escape it.

1028
01:37:47,471 --> 01:37:50,871
You will unite, or you will fall.

1029
01:37:51,271 --> 01:37:55,372
Each race is bound to
this fate, this one doom.

1030
01:37:57,372 --> 01:38:00,672
Bring forth the ring, Frodo.

1031
01:38:14,972 --> 01:38:16,572
So it is true.

1032
01:38:26,373 --> 01:38:27,873
<i>The ring of power...</i>

1033
01:38:29,973 --> 01:38:31,473
<i>The doom of men...</i>

1034
01:38:34,073 --> 01:38:36,073
In a dream...

1035
01:38:37,873 --> 01:38:40,973
...I saw the eastern sky grow dark...

1036
01:38:41,273 --> 01:38:42,973
...but in the West a pale light lingered.

1037
01:38:43,774 --> 01:38:45,574
A voice was crying:

1038
01:38:45,874 --> 01:38:48,674
"Your doom is near at hand.

1039
01:38:49,874 --> 01:38:52,474
Isildur's bane is found."

1040
01:38:54,604 --> 01:38:56,004
(The Ring)
[Black Speech] <i>Sherkuk-ishi</i>
[English] In your blood

1041
01:38:56,474 --> 01:38:58,274
Isildur's bane.

1042
01:38:59,071 --> 01:38:59,174
Boromir!

1043
01:38:59,135 --> 01:39:02,904
(Gandalf)
[Black Speech] <i>Ash nazg durbatulûk...</i>
[English] One ring to rule them all...

1044
01:39:00,484 --> 01:39:03,184
{\an8} (The Ring)
{\an8} [Black Speech] <i>Shre nazg golugranu kilmi-nudu...</i>
{\an8} [English] Three Rings for the Elven-kings under the sky...

1045
01:39:02,904 --> 01:39:06,614
(Gandalf)
[Black Speech] <i>...Ash nazg gimbatul...</i>
[English] ...One ring to find them...

1046
01:39:06,438 --> 01:39:10,701
{\an8} (The Ring)
{\an8} [Black Speech] <i>Ombi kuzd-durbagu... shirku</i>
{\an8} [English] Seven for the Dwarf-lords... blood

1047
01:39:06,824 --> 01:39:09,995
(Gandalf)
[Black Speech] <i>...Ash nazg thrakatulûk...</i>
[English] ...One ring to bring them all...

1048
01:39:11,019 --> 01:39:14,481
{\an8} (The Ring)
{\an8} [Black Speech] <i>Ash Burz-Durbagu burzum-ishi...</i>
{\an8} [English] One for the Dark lord on his dark throne...

1049
01:39:12,905 --> 01:39:17,225
(Gandalf)
[Black Speech] <i>...Agh burzum-ishi krimpatul.</i>
[English] ...and in the darkness bind them.

1050
01:39:23,375 --> 01:39:27,075
Never before has any voice uttered the
words of that tongue here in Imladris.

1051
01:39:27,475 --> 01:39:30,975
I do not ask your pardon, Master Elrond...

1052
01:39:31,275 --> 01:39:33,275
...for the black speech of Mordor...

1053
01:39:33,675 --> 01:39:34,975
...may yet be heard...

1054
01:39:35,276 --> 01:39:38,076
...in every corner of the West!

1055
01:39:38,376 --> 01:39:40,976
The ring is altogether evil.

1056
01:39:41,476 --> 01:39:42,876
It is a gift.

1057
01:39:43,676 --> 01:39:45,576
A gift to the foes of Mordor.

1058
01:39:46,276 --> 01:39:48,276
Why not use this ring?

1059
01:39:48,576 --> 01:39:51,276
Long has my father,
the Steward of Gondor...

1060
01:39:51,576 --> 01:39:55,676
...kept the forces of Mordor at bay.
By the blood of our people...

1061
01:39:56,176 --> 01:39:58,276
...are your lands kept safe.

1062
01:40:00,076 --> 01:40:04,277
Give Gondor the weapon of the enemy.
Let us use it against him.

1063
01:40:04,483 --> 01:40:07,497
You cannot wield it. None of us can.

1064
01:40:09,077 --> 01:40:12,977
The one ring answers to Sauron alone.
It has no other master.

1065
01:40:13,377 --> 01:40:16,777
And what would a ranger
know of this matter?

1066
01:40:17,077 --> 01:40:18,977
This is no mere ranger.

1067
01:40:20,077 --> 01:40:23,577
He is Aragorn, son of Arathorn.

1068
01:40:24,277 --> 01:40:27,078
You owe him your allegiance.

1069
01:40:31,278 --> 01:40:33,178
Aragorn.

1070
01:40:34,978 --> 01:40:37,778
This is Isildur's heir?

1071
01:40:40,116 --> 01:40:42,816
And heir to the throne of Gondor.

1072
01:40:44,358 --> 01:40:46,258
[Sindarin] <i>Havo dad, Legolas.</i>
[English] Sit down, Legolas.

1073
01:40:49,778 --> 01:40:52,579
Gondor has no king.

1074
01:40:54,579 --> 01:40:56,179
Gondor needs no king.

1075
01:41:02,879 --> 01:41:04,318
Aragorn is right.

1076
01:41:05,107 --> 01:41:06,379
We cannot use it.

1077
01:41:07,579 --> 01:41:10,293
You have only one choice.

1078
01:41:11,179 --> 01:41:13,479
The ring must be destroyed.

1079
01:41:18,780 --> 01:41:20,453
What are we waiting for?

1080
01:41:26,530 --> 01:41:31,642
[Black Speech] <i>Daghburz-ishi makha, ghurarmu shirku.</i>
[English] In the land of Mordor, a sacrifice of blood.

1081
01:41:33,577 --> 01:41:36,533
The ring cannot be destroyed, 
Gimli, son of Gloin...

1082
01:41:36,780 --> 01:41:40,003
...by any craft that we here possess.

1083
01:41:41,580 --> 01:41:45,157
The ring was made in
the fires of Mount Doom.

1084
01:41:45,981 --> 01:41:49,581
Only there can it be unmade.

1085
01:41:50,881 --> 01:41:53,281
It must be taken deep into Mordor...

1086
01:41:53,581 --> 01:41:57,881
...and cast back into the fiery
chasm from whence it came.

1087
01:41:57,286 --> 01:42:00,321
[Black Speech] <i>Makha gulshu darulu.</i>
[English] Where the Shadows lie.

1088
01:42:00,587 --> 01:42:01,903
One of you...

1089
01:42:03,081 --> 01:42:04,530
...must do this.

1090
01:42:08,181 --> 01:42:10,512
One does not simply walk into Mordor.

1091
01:42:12,782 --> 01:42:16,282
Its black gates are guarded
by more than just orcs.

1092
01:42:17,359 --> 01:42:20,625
There is evil there that does not sleep.

1093
01:42:21,482 --> 01:42:25,582
The great eye is ever-watchful.

1094
01:42:26,582 --> 01:42:28,482
It is a barren wasteland...

1095
01:42:28,765 --> 01:42:32,065
...riddled with fire, and ash and dust.

1096
01:42:32,582 --> 01:42:35,991
The very air you breathe
is a poisonous fume.

1097
01:42:36,683 --> 01:42:40,783
Not with 10,000 men could you do this.
It is folly.

1098
01:42:41,310 --> 01:42:43,703
Have you heard nothing
Lord Elrond has said?

1099
01:42:44,374 --> 01:42:45,645
The ring must be destroyed.

1100
01:42:45,883 --> 01:42:48,283
And I suppose you think
you are the one to do it!

1101
01:42:48,376 --> 01:42:52,876
And if we fail, what then? What happens
when Sauron takes back what is his?

1102
01:42:53,415 --> 01:42:58,027
I will be dead before I see the
ring in the hands of an elf!

1103
01:43:00,783 --> 01:43:03,184
Never trust an elf!

1104
01:43:04,484 --> 01:43:10,084
Do you not understand? While you bicker
amongst yourselves, Sauron's power grows!

1105
01:43:10,584 --> 01:43:13,384
None can escape it!
You'll all be destroyed!

1106
01:43:13,934 --> 01:43:16,714
[Black Speech] <i>Ash nazg durbatulûk...</i>
[English] One ring to rule them all...

1107
01:43:16,714 --> 01:43:19,224
[Black Speech] <i>...Ash nazg gimbatul.</i>
[English] ...One ring to find them.

1108
01:43:19,234 --> 01:43:21,324
[Black Speech] <i>Ash nazg durbatulûk...</i>
[English] One ring to rule them all...

1109
01:43:21,334 --> 01:43:23,434
[Black Speech] <i>...Ash nazg gimbatul.</i>
[English] ...One ring to find them.

1110
01:43:23,434 --> 01:43:25,424
[Black Speech] <i>Ash nazg durbatulûk...</i>
[English] One ring to rule them all...

1111
01:43:25,434 --> 01:43:27,635
[Black Speech] <i>...Ash nazg gimbatul.</i>
[English] ...One ring to find them.

1112
01:43:27,635 --> 01:43:29,535
[Black Speech] <i>Ash nazg durbatulûk...</i>
[English] One ring to rule them all...

1113
01:43:32,302 --> 01:43:33,786
I will take it.

1114
01:43:36,485 --> 01:43:37,968
I will take it.

1115
01:43:44,785 --> 01:43:47,097
I will take the ring to Mordor.

1116
01:43:56,086 --> 01:43:57,186
Though...

1117
01:44:00,386 --> 01:44:02,186
...I do not know the way.

1118
01:44:04,186 --> 01:44:08,286
I will help you bear this
burden, Frodo Baggins...

1119
01:44:08,686 --> 01:44:11,986
...as long as it is yours to bear.

1120
01:44:13,186 --> 01:44:16,186
If by my life or death I can protect you...

1121
01:44:16,986 --> 01:44:18,287
...I will.

1122
01:44:21,587 --> 01:44:23,787
You have my sword.

1123
01:44:25,796 --> 01:44:27,687
And you have my bow.

1124
01:44:28,437 --> 01:44:30,687
And my ax.

1125
01:44:37,887 --> 01:44:40,105
You carry the fates of us all, little one.

1126
01:44:42,887 --> 01:44:46,388
If this is indeed the
will of the Council...

1127
01:44:47,088 --> 01:44:49,488
...then Gondor will see it done.

1128
01:44:52,039 --> 01:44:54,410
Mr. Frodo's not going
anywhere without me.

1129
01:44:54,435 --> 01:44:56,649
No indeed it is hardly
possible to separate you...

1130
01:44:56,674 --> 01:45:00,934
...even when he is summoned to a
secret council and you are not.

1131
01:45:02,427 --> 01:45:04,227
Oy. We're coming too!

1132
01:45:06,488 --> 01:45:09,188
You'll have to send us home
tied up in a sack to stop us.

1133
01:45:09,188 --> 01:45:12,589
Anyway, you need people
of intelligence on this sort of...

1134
01:45:13,089 --> 01:45:14,289
...mission.

1135
01:45:14,637 --> 01:45:15,845
Quest.

1136
01:45:16,748 --> 01:45:17,815
Thing.

1137
01:45:19,505 --> 01:45:21,839
Well, that rules you out, Pip.

1138
01:45:23,539 --> 01:45:25,339
Nine companions.

1139
01:45:27,601 --> 01:45:28,939
So be it.

1140
01:45:29,744 --> 01:45:32,339
You shall be: The Fellowship of the Ring.

1141
01:45:33,022 --> 01:45:34,439
Great!

1142
01:45:35,420 --> 01:45:37,340
Where are we going?

